pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The bell on its neck glows and chimes when it shots fire through it. Although it acts spoiled with its Trainer, it is a capable and relentless brawler, it will keep battling until its foes lose their fighting spirits.

pokemonCollection.Name: Torterra
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Torterras travel in groups, mistaken as moving forests. Many pokemon make their nest on its back and live there for their entire lives. Ancient people thought that they lived on the back of a giant Torterra.

pokemonCollection.Name: Totodile
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Despite its small body, Totodile's jaws are very powerful. While it may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough strength to cause a serious injury. It needs proper discipline to control its biting urges

pokemonCollection.Name: Toucannon
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It can store and expel an extremely hot gas through its beak that ignites easily. The berry seeds it shoots can pierce boulders, leaving perfectly round holes on them. Fortunately, they nest deep in the jungle.

pokemonCollection.Name: Toxapex
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It crawls through the ocean floor, using its tentacles as a fortress. Its venom has the victim suffering for three days and nights, and even if it’s healed there are aftereffects for it is a powerful toxin.

pokemonCollection.Name: Toxel
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Toxel secrete poison through their skin, the closer they are to evolving, the brighter their skin color becomes. They need a lot of nurturing but are bad tempered and ill mannered so not many take the task.

pokemonCollection.Name: Toxicroak
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The toxin made in its poison sacs is pumped into the knuckle claws through tubes down its arms. Its toxins are so powerful that even a scratch from its knuckles could be fatal in a few hours.

pokemonCollection.Name: Toxtricity - Amped
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Commonly called “Amped Form”, its nature determines its evolution, If a Toxel is extroverted it will evolve to be a short-tempered Toxtricity. They emit high pitched sounds and let out powerful discharges to provoke others.

pokemonCollection.Name: Toxtricity - Low Key
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Commonly called “Low Key Form”, its nature determines its evolution, If a Toxel is introverted it will evolve to be a chill Toxtricity. They emit low pitched sounds and look down on others who try to provoke them.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tranquill
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: During war and old times people made use of Tranquil’s sense of location to send letters. It will never fail to find it’s way back home. They like quiet forests and enjoy to relax in the peace and quiet.

pokemonCollection.Name: Trapinch
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Their nest is like a bowl pit dug in sand. Trapinches wait for prey to tumble down their pit, later to be crushed between this Pokemon’s jaws. Beware of them as their bite can cause serious damage.

pokemonCollection.Name: Treecko
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They climb trees with their spiked feet. They remain cool under stress, calmed under pressure and collected when endangered. They are found protecting the trees ferociously.

pokemonCollection.Name: Trevenant
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Using its roots as a nervous system it controls the trees in the forest. It’s kind to the Pokemon that reside inside its body but it is ruthless to anyone that harms its forest, turning them into haunted trees forever.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tropius
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It is very common in humid and hot regions. It can grow back the fruit it has eaten. Mothers prefer Tropius fruits to feed their children as it is more nutritive and sweet. They are mellow and friendly Pokemon.

pokemonCollection.Name: Trubbish
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokemon. It belches a poison gas, breathing it will leave you sick in bed for a week. It loves filthy places.

pokemonCollection.Name: Trumbeak
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: This Pokemon bends its beak to produce a variety of sounds, much to the annoyance of the neighbors. It also shoots a burst of berry seeds to its foes, prey, or an unsuspecting passerby.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tsareena
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Tsareena's elegant appearance is only matched by its boastful fight spirit. It is known for disobeying any Trainer giving it orders it dislikes, and will celebrate its victories by kicking its defeated foes while laughing.

pokemonCollection.Name: Turtonator
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It leaves in the volcanic areas of Alola, where it disguises itself among the rocks, waiting for prey to step on it to detonate an explosion. The hole on its chest is a weak point, but it is very difficult to access.

pokemonCollection.Name: Turtwig
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It makes its home close to lakes, although it is rare to find one. The shell on its back is made of hardened soil and should be moist for it to be healthy. It uses photosynthesis to get energy.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tympole
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They appear in great numbers on marshes and ponds after a heavy rainfall. They warn others of danger and predators by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tynamo
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: These Pokemon move in schools. They have an electricity-storing organ at their sides but they can’t generate their own power. They only discharge electricity if they are in danger.

pokemonCollection.Name: Type Null
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: A synthetic Pokemon made by the Aether Foundation. Currently only three specimens exist in cryogenic stasis, but they are deemed too dangerous even with a limiter helmet on. They must never be reanimated.

pokemonCollection.Name: Typhlosion
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Very rare to see in the wild. It hides behind a shimmering heat haze created using its fire. Typhlosion can create eruptions and explosive blasts that can burn everything to the ground.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tyranitar - Mega
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The power of the Mega Stone is so overwhelming it splits its back open. It becomes overwhelmed by its ferocious instincts and it’s unclear if it can even hear its Trainer through the pain and rage.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tyranitar
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Its body is hardly damaged by any attack, so it’s always eager to fight. They are extremely strong, their rage can change landscapes. Tyranitars are insolents, rebels and they care about no one.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tyrantrum
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Nothing could stop this Pokemon 100 million years ago, it was a prehistoric king. Thanks to its giant jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, this Pokemon takes orders from no one.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tyrogue
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Tyrogue is an energetic, competitive and fearless Pokemon that’s always looking to get stronger, fighting any enemies even if it looses. They attack anyone, any day, anytime, everyday, without warning.

pokemonCollection.Name: Tyrunt
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: This Pokemon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild. Many of the researchers that brought it back were attacked by its powerful jaws.

pokemonCollection.Name: Umbreon
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Umbreon evolved from exposure to the moon’s energy pulses. It lurks in darkness and waits for its foes to move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack. Its fur is drenched with poison.

pokemonCollection.Name: Unfezant
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Males swing the beautiful plumage on their heads to threaten others and to court females. Although less visually appealing, females are better at flying. Once they form a pair they are mated for life.

pokemonCollection.Name: Unown
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: There are depictions of it in ancient ruins. When Unowns are gathered together, it is said that a strange power capable of anything emerges. They are all shaped like letters, each one of them with a unique power.

pokemonCollection.Name: Ursaring
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They are incredibly strong, great climbers and posses an amazing sense of smell. They snap trees and feed on their fruit as they eat quite a lot. A forest full of scratched trees marks the territory of Ursarings.

pokemonCollection.Name: Uxie
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: In the myths of Sinnoh they talk about three beings that came out from the same egg, the yellow one was the being of knowledge. Together they shaped the human race to be complete.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vanillish
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Snowy mountains are this Pokemon’s habitat. It conceals itself from enemy eyes by creating many small ice bundles and hiding around them. It may attach itself to the ceiling of ice caves to hide around the ice.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vanillite
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: This Pokemon were born from icicles that bathed in the energy of the morning sun. It uses snow to cover its head and protect it from melting. They are playful and love to make snow fall around them.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vanilluxe
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It grew a new head with evolution, and they get along really well. They need to drink a lot of water in order to keep cool outside a gelid weather. If both heads get angry they will expel a terrible blizzard around.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vaporeon
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Vaporeon underwent through a strange mutation, it grew fins and gills that allow it to live underwater. This Pokemon has the ability to become translucent when it dives underwater.

pokemonCollection.Name: Venipede
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Incredibly aggressive for a Pokemon that size. It uses the feelers on it’s front and back to locate things around. Its bite injects a potent venom, enough to deter the large bird Pokemon that try to prey on it.

pokemonCollection.Name: Venomoth
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They are plentiful in forests but only come out at night. They possess an incredible eyesight and are attracted to light sources. Their wings scatter a toxic powder which they use to immobilize their prey.

pokemonCollection.Name: Venonat
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It lives in the holes of trees in dense forests and jungles. Its large eyes never fail to spot even minuscule prey. Sometimes Venonat uses its powers to confuse travelers and make them lose their way.

pokemonCollection.Name: Venusaur - Mega
pokemonCollection.DexDescription:
With the power of the Mega Stone, this Pokemon grows taller and thicker. It’s bark and skin are now impervious to the elements.
Its demeanor becomes even more serious and determined.

pokemonCollection.Name: Venusaur
pokemonCollection.DexDescription:
Venusaur's flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of sun light. The flower’s aroma soothes the emotions of others.
If you find one in the wild, it must be the protector of the area.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vespiquen
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: This Pokemon is female only. It raises grubs in the holes in its body and secretes pheromones to control Combee to fight and gather honey for her. It is a royal Pokemon that won’t take orders from anyone.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vibrava
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: This Pokemon’s vibrations can cause severe headaches or even fainting. If their prey faints, they proceed to melt them with acid. Vibrava's wings are still growing, making it a clumsy flier with low endurance.

pokemonCollection.Name: Victini
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: On tournament days, Trainers eat a “V” shaped apple as a sign of good luck. It is unknown if it has anything to do with this Pokemon.

pokemonCollection.Name: Victreebel
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They live together in small groups at tropical areas. Victreebel uses a sweet honey-like smell to lure and attract prey. They also use their long vines to rustle bushes around. They are territorial and aggressive.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vigoroth
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They are always agitated, anxious, excited or upset, rampaging over anything. They can’t be still and they can’t sleep. They get angry if they get bored and violent if there is no activity for them.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vikavolt
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The electricity it shoots through its jaws is very dangerous, it zaps bird Pokemon trying to eat it. Its flight is peculiar, for it bends in a 90° angle or flies backwards without a problem.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vileplume
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It lives in marshlands and jungles where it’s often mistaken for local flora. The air around a Vileplume turns yellow with the powder it releases as it walks. The pollen is highly toxic and causes paralysis.

pokemonCollection.Name: Virizion
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: An old tale in Unova mentions four Pokemon that fought against an evil army. The most beautiful of them was also the most swift and graceful in combat, it created an army of trees that won the battle.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vivillon
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The patterns on this Pokemon’s wings depend on the climate it grows and the flowers it feeds on. A famous Pokemon breeder made one develop a Pokeball pattern, it was sold for a million dollars.

pokemonCollection.Name: Volbeat
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The male of its species. Their tail shines bright during the night, drawing geometric shapes in the sky. Volbeats live in swarms around clean ponds. They are attracted to Illumise's sweet aroma.

pokemonCollection.Name: Volcanion
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: In the early days of world exploring, there are records of an entire mountain blowing up in a cloud of steam. The explorers claimed that a creature in the fog was responsible.

pokemonCollection.Name: Volcarona
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of its battles, since it uses six wings to scatter blazing scales. There are stories of how its fire saved villages during winter and how it shone like the sun over the mountains.

pokemonCollection.Name: Voltorb
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They live near factories and electric generators. It bears an uncanny and unexplained resemblance to a Pokeball. Since it explodes at the slightest provocation, even veteran trainers treat it with caution.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vullaby
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: This is a female-only species. They stay with their Mandibuzz mothers from birth until they can finally fly. They feed on the carrion meat the mothers bring back to the nest and keep the bones to make accessories.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vulpix - Alolan
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The Vulpix who became stranded in Alola had to change type in order to survive. Alola’s local name for this Pokemon is Keokeo. They use their tails as a fan to cool themselves in hot climates.

pokemonCollection.Name: Vulpix
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It is born with just one tail. As it grows, its single white tail gains color and splits into six. It is quite warm and cuddly - very popular with the ladies . It is, however, uncommon to see one in the wild.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wailmer
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Wailmer has a playful nature. They can store water inside their body to inflate like a ball and bounce, then startle people by snorting the water from their nostrils. This Pokemon needs lots of food everyday.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wailord
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The largest Pokemon known to date. Wailords weight is really light so they can dive almost 10,000 feet with one breath. They live in open ocean herding fish to swallow in one gulp. They are used to being free.

pokemonCollection.Name: Walrein
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The leader of the herd is a powerful Walrein. They are very aggressive and will protect their herd even at the cost of their lives. Their tusks can shatter giant blocks of ice. It is relentless and unpredictable.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wartortle
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Its large tail is covered with rich, thick fur that deepens in color with age. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this Pokemon’s tough attitude in battle. It is a good hunter underwater.

pokemonCollection.Name: Watchog
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Their fur has a luminescent property. They make the patterns on their bodies glow in order to threaten predators. Their keen eyesight allows them to see in the dark. They are also good diggers.

pokemonCollection.Name: Weavile
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four that hunt prey with impressive coordination. They leave claw marks and patterns to indicate their territory. It is devious and loves to cause trouble.

pokemonCollection.Name: Weedle
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Often found in forests eating leaves. It has a sharp, venomous stinger on its head for defense. It has an acute sense of smell to find food, and its bright-colored body is intended to warn off predators.

pokemonCollection.Name: Weepinbell
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It sprays its stun powder to immobilize a prey coming close to it, then eats it calmly. If the prey is bigger than itself, it uses its sharp leaves to slice it into smaller pieces. Beware of the toxic liquid in its mouth.

pokemonCollection.Name: Weezing - Galarian
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: This Pokemon eats the contamination in the air, and instead of droppings, it expels clean air. Its Galar Form was first spotted long ago when factories polluted the City.

pokemonCollection.Name: Weezing
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They are considered a pest in urban areas. They wait until night to roam and eat from the trash cans in the neighborhood. If it finds a filthy and unkempt house it will make its nest in there.

pokemonCollection.Name: Whimsicott
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Riding whirlwinds, they appear and disappear. These Pokemon sneak through even the smallest gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief the balls of white fluff it leaves behind reveal its presence.

pokemonCollection.Name: Whirlipede
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It is usually motionless, when it is attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent with its body full of poison spikes. Inside it is storing energy for evolving, which normally takes a few months.

pokemonCollection.Name: Whiscash
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Dangerous and territorial, they claim entire ponds as their homes and will crush whoever dares to dive in with earthquakes. They eat anything alive in their pond or swamp. They have learned to foretell real tremors.

pokemonCollection.Name: Whismur
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Their timid voice is barely audible, however, if it senses danger, they start crying loud enough to deafen anyone nearby. Their own noise scares them even more, so they cry harder until their ear covers shut.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wigglytuff
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Its fur is extremely fine and conveys an image of luxury. Its body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck the air and inflate itself to an enormous size. It is a favorite pet and a nurse Pokemon.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wimpod
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They are curious but incredibly cowardly Pokemon. They are easily startled and will shoot a stenchy liquid as a warning. Even so, they are highly valued due to their ability to eat and clean any garbage.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wingull
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They carry prey and precious items in their beaks, hiding them in strange locations. They nest in sheer cliffs at the sea’s edge. They often harass fishing boats to steal an easy meal for themselves.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wishiwashi (Swarm Form)
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: A school of Wishiwashi is the demon of the sea. Even Gyarados flee in terror when one approaches. Since it is formed by lots of members, it’s impossible to control. They disband after the threat is “neutralized”.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wishiwashi
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: People and Pokemon enjoy this tiny Pokemon's meat. Their eyes shine as a distress signal, other members of its species will travel far and wide to attend the call for help. When this happens you must run.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wobbuffet
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Wobbuffet looks somewhat deflated until it senses an aggressor, then it inflates. It will do nothing besides endure and counter attacks. It always keeps its black tail hidden, the reasons are still a mystery.

pokemonCollection.Name: Woobat
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It lives in dark forests and caves. Emits ultrasonic waves from its nose it learns about its surroundings. The two small eyes it has get covered by its own fur. It clings to trees and cave walls to sleep at night.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wooloo
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Woolo's wool is incredibly resilient, it serves as a cushion when they fall from high mountain cliffs. They need to be sheared or their wool will be too heavy to move. A sweater made with this wool will last for a lifetime.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wooper
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Inhabits cold water sources and only comes out during the evening when the land has cooled, to find something to eat. Under this ideal environment it has rarely been seen at its evolved stage.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wormadam - Grass
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: When Burmy evolved, its Grass cloak became a part of its body. For this reason there are many variations in body and type. It is a calm Pokemon that loves flowers. This Pokemon is female only.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wormadam - Ground
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: When Burmy evolved, its Sand cloak became a part of its body. For this reason there are many variations in body and type. It is a calm Pokemon that loves odd-shaped stones. This Pokemon is female only.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wormadam - Steel
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: When Burmy evolved, its Trash cloak became a part of its body. For this reason there are many variations in body and type. It is a calm Pokemon that loves foil wrapping. This Pokemon is female only.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wurmple
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It uses the spikes on its rear to peel the trees and feed on their sap. Their feet have suction pads to climb easily. Wurmples are plentiful and live in forests, but they are often attacked by bird Pokemon.

pokemonCollection.Name: Wynaut
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Its face always appears to be happy, but Wynaut can be deceitful. You can only discern its true emotions through its tail. They live together in caves and bump into each other to gain strength.

pokemonCollection.Name: Xatu
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Xatu is known to stand motionless while staring at the sun all day long. Some people revere it as a mystical Pokemon out of their belief that Xatus have the power to see into the future.

pokemonCollection.Name: Xerneas
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: A Kalos legend tells about the eternal struggle between life and death. In the story an ancient King tried to obtain eternal life and the power to make its loved ones live again.

pokemonCollection.Name: Xurkitree
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: My superiors are furious. A lot of money had to be used to cover the damages UB-03 dealt in the power plant. On the bright side, it seems a lot livelier now that it appears to have recharged.

pokemonCollection.Name: Yamask - Galarian
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It’s said that this Pokemon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to the dark energy of a spirit. The clay slab seems to be absorbing Yamask's power that’s why it is so pale.

pokemonCollection.Name: Yamask
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: This Pokemon arose from the spirit of a human or a Pokemon that died in the past and was buried with special ceremonies. Each one carries a mask that looks like the face it had in life. A sad Pokemon that weeps often.

pokemonCollection.Name: Yamper
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Its energy and big smile make this Pokemon very popular as a herding dog. When it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail. It loves to fetch balls and if you give it some treats it will love you forever.

pokemonCollection.Name: Yanma
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It lives near water sources. Its eyes can see 360 degrees without even moving. Yanma is a great flyer capable of making sudden stops and turning midair to quickly chase down targeted prey.

pokemonCollection.Name: Yanmega
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It goes back to its prehistoric roots. It is a lot more violent than its pre-evolved form. Its jaw power is incredible and it is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed. This Pokemon can be brutal

pokemonCollection.Name: Yungoos
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: This Pokemon was brought to Alola in an attempt to eradicate Ratatta. It spends all day searching for prey and it’s constantly hungry. when the sun sets it falls asleep right where it was standing.

pokemonCollection.Name: Yveltal
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: A Kalos legend tells about the eternal struggle between life and death. The main tale is about a King full of grief and hate who built a doomsday machine to kill everyone in the world.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zacian - Crown
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: There is a legend about a mighty sword able to cut down anything with a single strike, it became known as the Fairy King’s Sword, and it inspired awe in friend and foe alike.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zacian
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: There is a legend of a heroine who through sheer might wielded the blade of heroes and vanquished a great evil away.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zamazenta - Crown
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: There is a legend about a mighty shield able to deflect any attack, it became known as the Fighting Master’s Shield, not even the largest creatures could go through it.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zamazenta
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: There is a legend of a hero who through sheer might wielded the shield of heroes to protect the people from the greatest evil.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zangoose
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The sole desire to battle Sevipers is embedded in their genes, they have been rivals since forever. Zangoose is a very agile quadruped, standing up on two legs only when ready to fight.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zapdos
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The myth tells of a bird who lived inside the thunderstorms of the region. It covered itself in lightning while flying in the dark clouds. A news report said it was involved in the closure of an energy plant.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zebstrika
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It is very ill tempered and wild, there have been very few cases of it being successfully tamed. It can shoot lightning from it’s mane in all directions. If you try to mount it without warning it will shock you.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zekrom
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: An old rock tablet full of ancient symbols tells the story of two brothers. One of them wanted a world of ideals built with the energy of the young. The rest of the stone is broken as if struck by lightning.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zeraora
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: An unfriendly creature was spotted in Alola, witnesses mentioned it electrified its claws and tore its foes apart with them. It disappeared into the wilderness and has not been reported again.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zigzagoon - Galarian
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Zigzagoons raised in Galar grow to be punks. If they see another Pokemon, they will purposely run into them to start a fight. The only way to calm them down is with a lot of loud noise.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zigzagoon
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They are extremely curious and want to know all about everything. Due to their innate curiosity, they usually find hidden objects. Sometimes they play dead to avoid being attacked.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zoroark
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They live in groups, their lair’s entrance is protected with their illusions and mirages. They have been known to fool entire towns with their tricks. Their illusions can hide their tails now but they remain mute.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zorua
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: They are very hard to find as they can transform into people and other Pokemon. They cannot speak when transformed and their tail remains visible. They ruin reputations by creating mischief in disguise.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zubat
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: It lives in dark caves all around the world. Prolonged exposure to the sun will make it unhealthy. It is blind but uses echolocation to find its way. At night, they leave their cave to feed on fruit and bug Pokemon.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zweilous
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The two heads do not get along with each other as they compete for food. For this reason , Zweilous usually eats more than it should. Touching it carelessly can get you attacked by one or both heads.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zygarde 10%
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: When 10% of the Zygarde Cells gather, they form this Pokemon, the more cells it gathers the more its strength will increase.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zygarde 50%
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Underground tunnels have been found all over the Kalos Region. There are rumors of a creature who lives in them that attacks people damaging the ecosystem.

pokemonCollection.Name: Zygarde 100%
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: The complete form of Zygarde

pokemonCollection.Name: Zygarde Cell
pokemonCollection.DexDescription: Only the the cores react to stimuli, the cells remain mostly inanimate. They gather in great numbers to create and strengthen Zygarde.
